DESCRIPTION:Event Types: Volunteer/Work Party<br>Building/Room #: Meet t
 he work party at the Black Sun sculpture in front of the Seattle Asian M
 useum. There will be signs around the park to help.<br>Neighborhoods: Ca
 pitol Hill\,North Capitol Hill<br>Location Type: Outdoor<br>Parks: Volun
 teer Park<br>Sponsoring Organization: Volunteer Park Trust<br>Contact: H
 annah<br>Contact Email: admin@volunteerparktrust.org<br>Site Contact Det
 ails: Hannah (admin@volunteerparktrust.org)<br>Audience: Adults\,Childre
 n\,Family\,Senior\,Teen<br>Pre-Register: No<br>Cost: Free<br>Link: https
 ://www.volunteerparktrust.org/events/springrestoration2026<br><br>Spring
  Restoration Day is back! Join your friends and neighbors for this exten
 ded version of our 2nd Saturday work party! We&#8217\;ll be mulching\, w
 eeding\, and maybe even planting a larger area within the park for this 
 event to beautify Volunteer Park for everyone to enjoy. This is a great 
 event for kids and families. <br><br>Meet us at the Black Sun Sculpture 
 across from Seattle Asian Art Museum at 10:00 AM on Saturday.  If you ar
 rive late\, look for our green signboard telling you where in the park w
 e will be working.<br><br>We will provide the gloves and tools.<br><br>P
 lease note\, no RSVP is necessary\, but helpful for a headcount of volun
 teers to prepare for. Anyone is welcome to stop by and help. Thanks&#821
 2\;we&#8217\;ll see you in the park!
