X-TRUMBA-CUSTOMFIELD;NAME="Detail image";ID=3052;TYPE=Image:<a href="htt
 ps://www.trumba.com/i/DgBAQTC5zun-JdqA3%2A1orzV9.jpg" target="_blank" re
 l="noopener" title="https://www.trumba.com/i/DgBAQTC5zun-JdqA3%2A1orzV9.
 jpg">www.trumba.com&#8230\;</a>
DTSTAMP:20260401T110311Z
DESCRIPTION:Event Types: Arts\,Community\,Museum/Gallery\,Music\,Special
  Events<br>Neighborhoods: Citywide\,Pioneer Square<br>Contact: Rana San<
 br>Contact Phone: (206) 256-6279<br>Contact Email: Rana.San@seattle.gov<
 br>Audience: All<br>Pre-Register: No<br>Cost: Free<br><br><p><strong>Joi
 n ARTS at King Street Station for <em>The Dreaming Room: Soundscapes for
  Deep Rest</em>\,</strong> <strong>a concert series&#160\;hosted by Step
 hanie Ann Ball\, with special guest Kiesha B. Free!</strong><br><br>This
  community-rooted concert series is designed to support nervous system r
 ecovery\, emotional release\, and collective connections through sound m
 editation\, music\, and storytelling. Come rest and connect over the cou
 rse of this renewing series\, every other month on the third Thursday&#1
 60\;between February and December.<br><br><em>We Still Dream a Future</e
 m>&#160\;is&#160\;a series of free public art activations\, installation
 s\, exhibitions\, performances\, and learning experiences designed to he
 lp us dream\, learn\, and grow\, taking place&#160\;throughout the Downt
 own core.<br><br><strong>SERIES SCHEDULE (3rd Thursdays)</strong>:<br>6:
 00 p.m. doors\, 6:30 p.m. music</p><ul> <li>February 19&#160\;&#8212\;&#
 160\;rejuvenation + renewal	</li><li>April 16&#160\;&#8212\;&#160\;creat
 ivity\, fun\, expansion	</li><li>June 18&#160\;&#8212\;&#160\;joyful\, w
 ondrous playtime	</li><li>August 20&#160\;&#8212\;&#160\;transitioning	<
 /li><li>October 15&#160\;&#8212\;&#160\;gratitude + reflection	</li><li>
 December 17&#160\;&#8212\;&#160\;celebration + releasing</li></ul><hr><p
 >Gallery hours are Wed. &#8211\; Sat. 11 a.m. &#8211\; 5 p.m.\; First Th
 ursdays 11 a.m. &#8211\; 8:00 p.m.<br><br><strong>Artist bios:<br><a hre
 f="https://stephanieannball.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Stephan
 ie Ann Ball</a></strong> is&#160\;a healing artist and sound meditation 
 facilitator. Her work sits at the intersection of therapeutic sound\, sc
 ience\, and well-being. Using sound meditation\, energy work\, and subco
 nscious reprogramming techniques\, Stephanie helps individuals and teams
  regulate the nervous system\, release stress\, and access states of cal
 m\, clarity\, and flow. The best part? It all starts with something easy
  and fun&#8212\;listening to music.<br><br><a href="https://kiesha.org/"
  target="_blank" rel="noopener"><strong>Kiesha B. Free</strong></a> is a
  masterful host\, speaker\, and independent cultural worker who moves th
 rough the world with heart\, humor\, and deep intention.&#160\;With a ba
 ckground spanning tech\, media\, and performance\, she brings people tog
 ether across differences - helping them reconnect with themselves\, each
  other\, and the impact they are meant to make.&#160\;Whether she&#8217
 \;s leading a global conference\, guiding a transformative conversation\,
  or delivering a keynote on bold self-reclamation\, Kiesha shows up as b
 oth mirror and spark - reflecting brilliance\, amplifying truth\, and ac
 tivating the cultural catalysts within us all.</p>
CATEGORIES:Arts and Culture
UID:http://uid.trumba.com/event/194911609
X-TRUMBA-LINK:https://www.seattle.gov/event-calendar?trumbaEmbed=view%3d
 event%26eventid%3d194911609
END:VEVENT
