DESCRIPTION:Event Types: Arts\,Education\,Training-Classes/Workshops<br>
 Neighborhoods: Citywide\,Online Event<br>Sponsoring Organization: Seattl
 e Office of Arts & Culture<br>Contact: Maija McKnight<br>Contact Phone: 
 206-684-7311<br>Contact Email: maija.mcknight@seattle.gov<br>Audience: A
 dults<br>Pre-Register: Yes<br>Cost: Free<br><br>Calling local artists wh
 o are interested in Public Art! Seattle Office of Arts &amp\; Culture of
 fers Public Art Boot Camp that is a training and workshop program for ar
 tists ready to translate their skills from studio art into the field of 
 public art. Up to 18 individual artists will be selected to participate 
 in this series of five workshops (and paid to do so).<br><br>Are you a l
 ocal studio artist who is interested in working within the field of publ
 ic art\, but haven&#8217\;t had success (or limited success) or don&#821
 7\;t know where to start? Public Art Boot Camp is program designed to pr
 ovide an in-depth orientation and provide building blocks and knowledge 
 of the ins and outs of public art. Space is limited in this series of 5 
 workshop training courses and so apply today!<br><br>Thinking about appl
 ying to Public Art Boot Camp\, but have questions about the program or a
 pplication process? Drop into the online information session to hear dir
 ectly from Project Managers about the program and process.
CATEGORIES:Arts and Culture
