DESCRIPTION:Neighborhoods: Ballard\,Belltown\,Cascade/Eastlake/South Lak
 e Union\,Columbia City\,Greenwood/Phinney Ridge\,Madison Park\,North of 
 Seattle\,Wallingford\,West Seattle Junction/Genesee Hill<br>Event Types:
  Community\,Gardening\,Special Events<br>Audience: Adults\,All\,Children
 \,Family\,Pets\,Senior\,Special Needs\,Teen<br>Sponsoring Organization: 
 Sno-Valley Senior Center<br>Contact: Kira Avery<br>Contact Phone: 425-33
 3-4152<br>Contact Email: kiraa@soundgenerations.org<br>Pre-Register: No<
 br>Cost: Free<br>Registration Details: For basket purchases and more inf
 ormation\, visit: https://snovalleysenior.org/spring-into-gardening/ or 
 call 425-333-4152.<br>Link: https://snovalleysenior.org/spring-into-gard
 ening/<br><br>Celebrate the season and get your garden growing at the Sn
 o-Valley Senior Center&#8217\;s beloved annual &#8220\;Spring Into Garde
 ning&#8221\; Plant Sale\, happening Friday\, May 1 and Saturday\, May 2 
 from 9:00 a.m. to 3:00 p.m. at the Sno-Valley Senior Center (4610 Stephe
 ns Ave\, just behind City Hall).<br><br>One of the largest plant sales o
 n the Eastside\, this community favorite features a wide variety of annu
 als\, perennials\, shrubs\, vegetables\, herbs\, fresh flowers\, and uni
 que garden art&#8212\;perfect for gardeners of all experience levels.<br
 ><br>Family-friendly fun continues on Saturday with a dedicated kids&#82
 17\; activity area\, where children can decorate and plant their own pot
 s to take home.<br><br>All proceeds from the event directly support prog
 rams and services at the Sno-Valley Senior Center\, helping local older 
 adults stay active\, connected\, and engaged.<br><br>Thank you to our ev
 ent sponsors\, Happy Valley Grange\, Lighthouse Plumbing\, North Bend Ac
 e Hardware\, and Carnation Co-Op!
