DESCRIPTION:Event Types: Arts\,Community\,Special Events<br>Neighborhood
 s: Citywide\,Pioneer Square<br>Contact: Rana San<br>Contact Phone: (206)
  256-6279<br>Contact Email: Rana.San@seattle.gov<br>Audience: All<br>Pre
 -Register: No<br>Cost: Free<br><br><p><strong>Join ARTS at King Street S
 tation for the&#160\;Mobile Book Fair and Zine Library</strong><strong>
 \,&#160\;a series of plaza pop ups</strong> <strong> hosted by Common Are
 a Maintenance.</strong><br><br>Free zines\, books\, artist-made publicat
 ions\, and participatory workshops furnish this book fair on the King St
 reet Station plaza. Featured zines and printed works explore hope for th
 e future through the lens of secret histories and overlooked stories fro
 m Seattle&#8217\;s pocket neighborhoods.<br><br>Join us for six pop ups 
 in 2026\, on the First Thursdays of May through September.<br><br><em>We
  Still Dream a Future</em>&#160\;is&#160\;a series of free public art ac
 tivations\, installations\, exhibitions\, performances\, and learning ex
 periences designed to help us dream\, learn\, and grow\, taking place&#1
 60\;throughout the Downtown core.<br><br><strong>SERIES SCHEDULE (1st Th
 ursdays &amp\; Summer Solstice)</strong>:</p><ul> <li>May 7	</li><li>Jun
 e 4	</li><li>June 20&#160\;&#8212\; LONGEST DAY	</li><li>July 2	</li><li
 >August 6	</li><li>September 3</li></ul><hr><p>Gallery hours are Wed. &#
 8211\; Sat. 11 a.m. &#8211\; 5 p.m.\; First Thursdays 11 a.m. &#8211\; 8
 :00 p.m.<br><br><strong>Organizer bio:</strong><br><strong><a href="http
 s://www.camseattle.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Common AREA Main
 tenance</a></strong> (CAM) is an artist run organization rooted in the b
 elief that creativity thrives through shared space\, collective care\, a
 nd public participation. CAM supports a growing community of artists\, p
 erformers\, writers\, organizers\, and neighbors by providing accessible
  and affordable spaces for experimentation\, dialogue\, and connection.<
 /p>
CATEGORIES:Arts and Culture
