DESCRIPTION:Building/Room #: Seattle Center Armory Loft 3 or Webex<br>Ev
 ent Types: Boards & Commissions<br>Neighborhoods: Citywide<br>Department
 /Organization: Seattle Center<br>Audience: Adults\,Children\,Family\,Sen
 ior\,Special Needs\,Teen<br>Department: Seattle Center<br>Website: http:
 //www.seattlecenter.com/<br>Contact: Kaori Kiyono<br>Contact Phone: 206-
 200-8935<br>Contact Email: kaori.kiyono2@seattle.gov<br>Pre-Register: Ye
 s<br>Registration Details: <p><strong>Public Comment Guide</strong></p><
 p>We accept public comments on matters pertaining to our agenda.</p><ul>
 	<li>Speakers should register either 1). by emailing the commission or 2
 ). by signing up in-person at the meeting itself in order to be recogniz
 ed by the Chair.</li></ul><p>&nbsp\; 1). To register\, send an email to 
 centercommission@seattle.gov with &ldquo\;public comment&rdquo\; in the 
 subject line by 10:00 AM on the day of the meeting.<strong> </strong></p
 ><p>2). Alternatively\, sign up to speak on the public comment sign-up s
 heet located inside the meeting room at least 15 minutes prior to each S
 eattle Center Advisory Commission meeting.</p><ul>	<li>Each speaker may 
 be allotted up to two minutes to speak.</li>	<li>In addition to topics o
 n the agenda\, the Chair may allow public comment on other topics.</li>	
 <li>If you are unable to attend the meeting in-person or remotely\, plea
 se submit written comments to <u>centercommission@seattle.gov</u></li></
 ul><br>Link: https://www.seattlecenter.com//about/advisory-commission<br
 ><br>The Seattle Center Advisory Commission is hereby constituted to ser
 ve as a citizen&#39\;s Oversight Committee for the Seattle Center projec
 t provided that the Commission&#39\;s oversight responsibilities shall n
 ot derogate from the responsibilities of Seattle Center or the legislati
 ve Authority of the City. The Oversight Committee shall report to the De
 partment\, the Mayor and the City Council on request from time-to-time r
 egarding progress in accomplishing the authorization contained herein an
 d in Ordinance 115593.<br><br>The Seattle Center Advisory Commission sha
 ll represent the interests of the people of Seattle by advising the Seat
 tle Center staff\, the Mayor and the City Council on policy matters that
  may affect Seattle Center. The Seattle Center Advisory Commission shall
  also provide the Seattle Center staff\, the Mayor and the City Council 
 with an ongoing assessment of the operations\, performances\, plans and 
 policies of the Seattle Center Department.
