DESCRIPTION:Event Types: Arts\,Community\,Music\,Special Events<br>Neigh
 borhoods: Citywide\,Pioneer Square<br>Contact: Rana San<br>Contact Phone
 : (206) 256-6279<br>Contact Email: Rana.San@seattle.gov<br>Audience: All
 <br>Pre-Register: No<br>Cost: Free<br><br><p><strong>Join ARTS at King S
 treet Station for <em>The Living Legacy of Joe Brazil</em></strong><stro
 ng>\,&#160\;a series of plaza concerts</strong> <strong> hosted by Joe B
 razil Legacy.</strong><br><br>A tribute to the enduring vision and impac
 t of legendary jazz musician\, educator\, and community builder Joe Braz
 il\, this concert series remembers a giant whose shoulders we stand upon
  to build our future\, featuring live music and dance on the King Street
  Station plaza.<br><br>Join us for four concerts in 2026\, on the First 
 Thursdays of June through September.<br><br><em>We Still Dream a Future<
 /em>&#160\;is&#160\;a series of free public art activations\, installati
 ons\, exhibitions\, performances\, and learning experiences designed to 
 help us dream\, learn\, and grow\, taking place&#160\;throughout the Dow
 ntown core.<br><br><strong>SERIES SCHEDULE (1st Thursdays)</strong>:</p>
 <ul> <li>June 4&#160\;&#8212\; Joe Brazil Legacy Tribute + Joe Brazil Le
 gacy House Band	</li><li>July 2&#160\;&#8212\;&#160\;&#8220\;Blues Man&#
 8221\; Johnny Moore +&#160\;CT Thompson	</li><li>August 6 &#8212\;&#160
 \;The Magic of Makini + Phyllis Talley	</li><li>September 3&#160\;&#8212
 \;&#160\;Lonnie Williams Then &amp\; Now + Medearis Dixson</li></ul><hr><
 p>Gallery hours are Wed. &#8211\; Sat. 11 a.m. &#8211\; 5 p.m.\; First T
 hursdays 11 a.m. &#8211\; 8:00 p.m.<br><br><strong>Organizer bio:</stron
 g><br><strong><a href="https://joebrazil.org/" target="_blank" rel="noop
 ener">Joe Brazil Legacy</a></strong> is built on years of hands-on exper
 ience producing deeply rooted\, intergenerational community events. Thes
 e gatherings have become beloved cultural touchstones in our community\,
  known not just for live music\, but for fostering connection\, pride\, 
 and purpose across generations.</p>
CATEGORIES:Arts and Culture
