DESCRIPTION:Event Types: Arts\,Community\,Music\,Special Events<br>Neigh
 borhoods: Citywide\,Pioneer Square<br>Contact: Rana San<br>Contact Phone
 : (206) 256-6279<br>Contact Email: Rana.San@seattle.gov<br>Audience: All
 <br>Pre-Register: No<br>Cost: Free<br><br><p><strong>Join ARTS at King S
 treet Station for <em>Setting of the Daybreak Star</em></strong><strong>
 \,&#160\;a series of plaza concerts</strong> <strong> hosted by United I
 ndians of All Tribes Foundation\, Daybreak Star Radio Network</strong><s
 trong>. June features a performance by Supaman!&#160\;</strong><br><br>T
 his series of events on the King Street Station Plaza creates an urban s
 anctuary where participants can gather in celebration as the day transit
 ions to evening. The programs&#160\;highlight Indigenous performers\, cr
 eating an accessible entry point for communities to engage with Native m
 usic and&#160\;cultural traditions.<br><br>Join us for four sessions in 
 2026\, on the second Thursdays of June through September.<br><br><em>We 
 Still Dream a Future</em>&#160\;is&#160\;a series of free public art act
 ivations\, installations\, exhibitions\, performances\, and learning exp
 eriences designed to help us dream\, learn\, and grow\, taking place&#16
 0\;throughout the Downtown core.<br><br><strong>SERIES SCHEDULE (2nd Thu
 rsdays)</strong>:</p><ul> <li>June 11&#160\;&#8212\; Supaman	</li><li>Ju
 ly 9&#160\;&#8212\; Ribbon Skirt	</li><li>August 13&#160\;&#8212\; The N
 eighborhood Kids	</li><li>September 10&#160\;&#8212\; TBA!</li></ul><hr>
 <p>Gallery hours are Wed. &#8211\; Sat. 11 a.m. &#8211\; 5 p.m.\; First 
 Thursdays 11 a.m. &#8211\; 8:00 p.m.<br><br><strong>Artist bio:</strong>
 <br>As a member of the &#8220\;Apsaalooke Nation&#8221\;\, <a href="http
 s://www.supamanhiphop.net/about" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><strong>
 Supaman</strong></a> makes his home on Aps&#225\;alooke lands in Montana
 . &#8220\;Supaman&#8221\; Is Christian Takes Gun Parrish\, a Native Amer
 ican dancer and innovative hip hop artist who has dedicated his life to 
 empowering and spreading a message of hope\, pride and resilience throug
 h his original art form. He has been the recipient of the 2017 MTV VMA a
 ward for &#8220\;Best Fight Against the System&#8221\;! He is also a Nam
 my &#8220\;Native American Music Award&#8221\; winner\, &#8220\;North Am
 erican Indigenous Image Award winner\, and &#160\;7 &#8220\;Tunney Award
  winner. He was awarded &#160\;The Aboriginal Peoples Choice Music Award
  in Canada for best video and was voted MTV&#8217\;s new Artist of the W
 eek! His nominations brought him home awards for Best Hip Hop Album and 
 Best Producer for the Indigenous Music Awards. His videos have received 
 millions of views on youtube and facebook which has put him in high dema
 nd touring extensively throughout the U.S.A and internationally. He has 
 performed for Google at the Google headquarters in San Francisco. He rec
 ently was asked to audition for America&#8217\;s Got Talent and the Broa
 dway play Hamilton. He is currently on tour around the country spreading
  the good medicine of resiliency\, love\, laughter and inclusion.<br><br
 ><strong>Organizer bio:</strong><br><a href="https://unitedindians.org/"
  target="_blank" rel="noopener"><strong>Daybreak Star Radio</strong></a>
  is<strong>&#160\;</strong>a Native American radio station with a sacred
  mission to Indigenize the airwaves. Their&#160\;team is 100% Native Ame
 rican\, with every staff member actively engaged in their tribal communi
 ties. Their managers bring diverse creative backgrounds as artists\, the
 atre workers\, and musicians\, infusing programming with authentic cultu
 ral perspectives. The station serves as a vital cultural hub for Native 
 American\, First Nations\, and Pacific Islander communities\,&#160\;show
 casing Indigenous artists and voices that are typically underrepresented
  in mainstream media. This commitment stems from their deep connections 
 to our heritage and ancestral knowledge systems.</p>
CATEGORIES:Arts and Culture
